'''Kodama-hiko no Mikoto''' (児玉彦命) is a deity of {{ill|Suwa Faith|ja|諏訪信仰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Faith|qq=}}, a traditional belief system rooted in the {{ill|Suwa Region|lt=Suwa Region|lt=Suwa region|ja|諏訪地方|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa region|qq=}} of [[:en:Nagano Prefecture|Nagano Prefecture]].

== Overview ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|170px|thumbnail|center|The first five generations of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}} lineage according to the ''Genealogy of the Moriya clan'' (洩矢神から八櫛神まで).]]
According to the genealogy of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}}, compiled during the early [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]], Kodama-hiko no Mikoto is described as follows:
<blockquote>
"The son of Katakurabe no Mikoto, a child of the Great Deity ({{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神|1=Takeminakata|2=ja|3=タケミナカタ|lt=Takeminakata|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata|qq=}}). Following the command of the Great Deity, he succeeded {{ill|Chikato|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikato|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=}} as the overseer of rituals and governance. He married Mitsutama-hime, daughter of {{ill|Moritachi no Kami|ja|守達神|1=Moritachi no Kami|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moritachi no Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Moritachi no Kami|qq=}}, and they bore Yasugami."<ref name="suwa">{{Cite web|title=Genealogy of the Moriya clan|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/1185913/24|publisher=Suwa Historical Association|year=1938|access-date=2023-12-04}}</ref><ref name="tikatousin">{{Cite web|title=Chikato and the Moriya Lineage|url=http://yatsu-genjin.jp/suwataisya/sanpo/tikatousin.htm|publisher=Yatsu Genjin|access-date=2023-12-04}}</ref>
</blockquote>

This makes Kodama-hiko no Mikoto the fourth generation of the Moriya lineage.<ref name="tikatousin"/><ref>''Continued Cultural Assets of Takabe,'' Takabe History Compilation Committee, 2006, p. 31.</ref>

== Lineage ==
Kodama-hiko no Mikoto is the child of {{ill|Katakurabe no Mikoto|ja|片倉辺命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katakurabe no Mikoto|qq=}}, with his mother unknown. He married {{ill|Mitsutama-hime no Kami|ja|美都多麻比売神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitsutama-hime no Kami|qq=}}, the daughter of {{ill|Moritachi no Kami|ja|守達神|1=Moritachi no Kami|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moritachi no Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Moritachi no Kami|qq=}}, and they had Yasugami, who is regarded as the fifth generation of the Moriya clan.<ref name="suwa"/>

== Shrines ==
Kodama-hiko no Mikoto is enshrined at the following locations:
* {{ill|Kodama-ishi Shrine|ja|児玉石神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kodama-ishi Shrine|qq=}} (Yunowaki, Suwa City, Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Taisan Shrine|lt=Taisan Shrine|lt=Taizan Shrine (Takamori)|ja|泰山神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taizan Shrine (Takamori)|qq=}} (Takamori Town, [[:en:Shimoina District, Nagano|Shimoina District, Nagano]], Nagano Prefecture)

