'''Kodama-hiko no Mikoto''' (児玉彦命) is a [[:en:Kami|kami]] worshiped in the {{ill|Suwa Region|lt=Suwa Region|lt=Suwa region|ja|諏訪地方|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Region|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 諏訪地域}} of [[:en:Nagano Prefecture|Nagano Prefecture]], as part of the {{ill|Suwa Faith|ja|諏訪信仰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Faith|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 諏訪神社|1=Suwa Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2370082}}.

== Overview ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|170px|thumbnail|{{Center|The first five generations of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}} as depicted in the genealogical text}}]]
According to the {{ill|Kaminaga Moriya clan Genealogy|ja|神長守矢氏系譜|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaminaga Moriya clan Genealogy|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, a genealogy of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}} compiled in the early [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]]:

<blockquote> {{ill|Oogami|ja|大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oogami|qq=|1=Ōkami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10937139}}’s child, {{ill|Katakurabe no Mikoto|ja|片倉辺命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katakurabe no Mikoto|qq=}}, begot Kodama-hiko no Mikoto, who succeeded the position of {{ill|Chikatojin|ja|千鹿頭神|1=Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatojin|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikatō-no-Kami|qq=}} in accordance with the divine words of Oogami. He married Mitutama-hime no Kami, the daughter of Moritatsu no Kami, and they bore Yatsukushin.<ref name="suwa">{{Cite book |title=Kaminaga Moriya clan Genealogy|author=Suwa Educational Association|year=1938|page=34|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/1185913/24}}</ref><ref name="tikatousin">[http://yatsu-genjin.jp/suwataisya/sanpo/tikatousin.htm Chikatojin (Genealogy of Moreya Clan)]</ref>
</blockquote>

As such, Kodama-hiko no Mikoto is regarded as the fourth generation in the genealogy of the Moriya clan.<ref name="tikatousin"/><ref>『続・高部の文化財』高部歴史編纂委員会編、2006th year 、31頁</ref>

== Genealogy ==
Kodama-hiko no Mikoto is the child of {{ill|Katakurabe no Mikoto|ja|片倉辺命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katakurabe no Mikoto|qq=}}, though his mother is unknown. His spouse, Mitutama-hime no Kami, the daughter of Moritatsu no Kami, bore him Yatsukushin, who is regarded as the fifth generation in the Moriya clan’s genealogy.<ref name="suwa"/>

== Shrines ==
Kodama-hiko no Mikoto is enshrined in the following locations:
* {{ill|Kodama-ishi Shrine|ja|児玉石神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kodama-ishi Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Yuno-waki, [[:en:Suwa, Nagano|Suwa City]], Nagano Prefecture)
* {{ill|Taisan Shrine|ja|泰山神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taisan Shrine|qq=}} ({{ill|Takamori Town|ja|高森町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamori Town|qq=|1=Takamorimachi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q31469}}, [[:en:Shimoina District, Nagano|Shimoina District]], Nagano Prefecture)

